{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019juJCVZpgrfKCxFKh7Ezcz","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: \"PRD-224.3\"\n3\ttitle: \"summarize_agent_run BuiltIn + run-summary in create_pr\"\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: ready\n6\tpriority: high\n7\teffort: s\n8\tcapability: moderate\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-224-harness-invariants-honest-state]]\"\n10\tdepends_on: []\n11\tblocks: []\n12\timpacts:\n13\t  - src/darkfactory/builtins.py\n14\t  - src/darkfactory/invoke.py\n15\t  - src/darkfactory/workflow.py\n16\t  - workflows/default/workflow.py\n17\t  - tests/test_builtins.py\n18\tworkflow: null\n19\ttarget_version: null\n20\tcreated: 2026-04-08\n21\tupdated: 2026-04-08\n22\ttags:\n23\t  - harness\n24\t  - invariants\n25\t  - hygiene\n26\t---\n27\t\n28\t# summarize_agent_run BuiltIn + run-summary in create_pr\n29\t\n30\t## Summary\n31\t\n32\tTwo pieces that compose together:\n33\t\n34\t1. A new `summarize_agent_run` BuiltIn that reads the most recent `InvokeResult` from the context, aggregates tool-call counts, and writes the summary into `ctx.run_summary`.\n35\t2. The `create_pr` BuiltIn checks for `ctx.run_summary` and appends it to the PR body if present.\n36\t\n37\tThis is a `[primitive]` — composable into any workflow's task list.\n38\t\n39\t## Requirements\n40\t\n41\t1. Add a `run_summary: str | None` field to `ExecutionContext` in `workflow.py`.\n42\t2. Expose tool-call counts in `InvokeResult` (in `invoke.py`). Parse the existing `_summarize_stream_event` output or the raw tool-call events to aggregate counts by tool name.\n43\t3. Create a new `summarize_agent_run` BuiltIn that:\n44\t   - Reads the most recent `InvokeResult` from the context.\n45\t   - Aggregates: workflow name, model, agent invocation count/retries, tool-call counts, test results, lint results, sentinel value.\n46\t   - Formats the summary as a markdown section.\n47\t   - Writes it to `ctx.run_summary`.\n48\t4. Modify `create_pr` BuiltIn to append `ctx.run_summary` to the PR body if it is not None.\n49\t5. Update the default workflow's task list to insert `summarize_agent_run` before `create_pr`.\n50\t6. If `summarize_agent_run` is not in the workflow (ctx.run_summary is None), `create_pr` produces the same PR body as today — no regression.\n51\t\n52\t## Technical Approach\n53\t\n54\t### `src/darkfactory/workflow.py`\n55\t\n56\tAdd field to `ExecutionContext`:\n57\t\n58\t```python\n59\t@dataclass\n60\tclass ExecutionContext:\n61\t    # ... existing fields ...\n62\t    run_summary: str | None = None\n63\t```\n64\t\n65\t### `src/darkfactory/invoke.py`\n66\t\n67\tExpose tool-call counts on `InvokeResult`:\n68\t\n69\t```python\n70\t@dataclass\n71\tclass InvokeResult:\n72\t    # ... existing fields ...\n73\t    tool_counts: dict[str, int] = field(default_factory=dict)\n74\t```\n75\t\n76\tParse tool-call events during invocation to populate `tool_counts`.\n77\t\n78\t### `src/darkfactory/builtins.py`\n79\t\n80\t```python\n81\tdef summarize_agent_run(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None:\n82\t    \"\"\"Aggregate tool-call counts and write a markdown summary to ctx.run_summary.\"\"\"\n83\t    result = ctx.last_invoke_result\n84\t    if result is None:\n85\t        return\n86\t\n87\t    lines = [\n88\t        \"## Harness execution summary\",\n89\t        \"\",\n90\t        f\"- **Workflow:** {ctx.workflow_name}\",\n91\t        f\"- **Model:** {ctx.model}\",\n92\t        f\"- **Agent invocations:** {_format_invocations(ctx)}\",\n93\t        f\"- **Tools used:** {_format_tool_counts(result.tool_counts)}\",\n94\t        f\"- **Sentinel:** {result.sentinel or 'none'}\",\n95\t    ]\n96\t    ctx.run_summary = \"\\n\".join(lines)\n97\t```\n98\t\n99\tModify `create_pr`:\n100\t\n101\t```python\n102\tdef create_pr(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None:\n103\t    body = _build_pr_body(ctx)\n104\t    if ctx.run_summary:\n105\t        body += \"\\n\\n\" + ctx.run_summary\n106\t    # ... existing gh pr create logic ...\n107\t```\n108\t\n109\t### `workflows/default/workflow.py`\n110\t\n111\tInsert `summarize_agent_run` in the task list just before `create_pr`.\n112\t\n113\t### Tests\n114\t\n115\t- Test `summarize_agent_run` with a mock context containing tool counts -> verify `ctx.run_summary` is set with correct format.\n116\t- Test `create_pr` with and without `ctx.run_summary` -> verify PR body is correct in both cases.\n117\t\n118\t## Acceptance Criteria\n119\t\n120\t- [ ] AC-1: `ExecutionContext` has a `run_summary` field.\n121\t- [ ] AC-2: `InvokeResult` exposes `tool_counts` dict.\n122\t- [ ] AC-3: `summarize_agent_run` BuiltIn produces a markdown summary with workflow, model, tool counts, and sentinel.\n123\t- [ ] AC-4: A PR opened by the default workflow includes the \"Harness execution summary\" section.\n124\t- [ ] AC-5: A workflow that omits `summarize_agent_run` produces the same PR body as before (no regression).\n125\t- [ ] AC-6: Unit tests pass for summary generation and PR body composition.\n126\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"52744e12-d8b3-437c-a43e-6547c29dff12","uuid":"b510d83c-f8a7-4538-bc0e-2ed456f9e62c","timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:16:00.809Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/prds/PRD-224.3-summarize-agent-run.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-224.3\"\ntitle: \"summarize_agent_run BuiltIn + run-summary in create_pr\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: high\neffort: s\ncapability: moderate\nparent: \"[[PRD-224-harness-invariants-honest-state]]\"\ndepends_on: []\nblocks: []\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/builtins.py\n  - src/darkfactory/invoke.py\n  - src/darkfactory/workflow.py\n  - workflows/default/workflow.py\n  - tests/test_builtins.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - invariants\n  - hygiene\n---\n\n# summarize_agent_run BuiltIn + run-summary in create_pr\n\n## Summary\n\nTwo pieces that compose together:\n\n1. A new `summarize_agent_run` BuiltIn that reads the most recent `InvokeResult` from the context, aggregates tool-call counts, and writes the summary into `ctx.run_summary`.\n2. The `create_pr` BuiltIn checks for `ctx.run_summary` and appends it to the PR body if present.\n\nThis is a `[primitive]` — composable into any workflow's task list.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Add a `run_summary: str | None` field to `ExecutionContext` in `workflow.py`.\n2. Expose tool-call counts in `InvokeResult` (in `invoke.py`). Parse the existing `_summarize_stream_event` output or the raw tool-call events to aggregate counts by tool name.\n3. Create a new `summarize_agent_run` BuiltIn that:\n   - Reads the most recent `InvokeResult` from the context.\n   - Aggregates: workflow name, model, agent invocation count/retries, tool-call counts, test results, lint results, sentinel value.\n   - Formats the summary as a markdown section.\n   - Writes it to `ctx.run_summary`.\n4. Modify `create_pr` BuiltIn to append `ctx.run_summary` to the PR body if it is not None.\n5. Update the default workflow's task list to insert `summarize_agent_run` before `create_pr`.\n6. If `summarize_agent_run` is not in the workflow (ctx.run_summary is None), `create_pr` produces the same PR body as today — no regression.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/workflow.py`\n\nAdd field to `ExecutionContext`:\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass ExecutionContext:\n    # ... existing fields ...\n    run_summary: str | None = None\n```\n\n### `src/darkfactory/invoke.py`\n\nExpose tool-call counts on `InvokeResult`:\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass InvokeResult:\n    # ... existing fields ...\n    tool_counts: dict[str, int] = field(default_factory=dict)\n```\n\nParse tool-call events during invocation to populate `tool_counts`.\n\n### `src/darkfactory/builtins.py`\n\n```python\ndef summarize_agent_run(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Aggregate tool-call counts and write a markdown summary to ctx.run_summary.\"\"\"\n    result = ctx.last_invoke_result\n    if result is None:\n        return\n\n    lines = [\n        \"## Harness execution summary\",\n        \"\",\n        f\"- **Workflow:** {ctx.workflow_name}\",\n        f\"- **Model:** {ctx.model}\",\n        f\"- **Agent invocations:** {_format_invocations(ctx)}\",\n        f\"- **Tools used:** {_format_tool_counts(result.tool_counts)}\",\n        f\"- **Sentinel:** {result.sentinel or 'none'}\",\n    ]\n    ctx.run_summary = \"\\n\".join(lines)\n```\n\nModify `create_pr`:\n\n```python\ndef create_pr(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None:\n    body = _build_pr_body(ctx)\n    if ctx.run_summary:\n        body += \"\\n\\n\" + ctx.run_summary\n    # ... existing gh pr create logic ...\n```\n\n### `workflows/default/workflow.py`\n\nInsert `summarize_agent_run` in the task list just before `create_pr`.\n\n### Tests\n\n- Test `summarize_agent_run` with a mock context containing tool counts -> verify `ctx.run_summary` is set with correct format.\n- Test `create_pr` with and without `ctx.run_summary` -> verify PR body is correct in both cases.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `ExecutionContext` has a `run_summary` field.\n- [ ] AC-2: `InvokeResult` exposes `tool_counts` dict.\n- [ ] AC-3: `summarize_agent_run` BuiltIn produces a markdown summary with workflow, model, tool counts, and sentinel.\n- [ ] AC-4: A PR opened by the default workflow includes the \"Harness execution summary\" section.\n- [ ] AC-5: A workflow that omits `summarize_agent_run` produces the same PR body as before (no regression).\n- [ ] AC-6: Unit tests pass for summary generation and PR body composition.\n","numLines":126,"startLine":1,"totalLines":126}}}
