{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VY5yvgKPwv2hRoH6LnF3Du","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Workflow execution engine — walks a workflow's tasks against a context.\n2\t\n3\tThe runner is the glue between every other module in the harness:\n4\t\n5\t- It holds an :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.ExecutionContext` and\n6\t  threads it through the task list.\n7\t- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.BuiltIn`, it looks up the\n8\t  named function in :data:`~darkfactory.builtins.BUILTINS` and calls\n9\t  it with the context + formatted kwargs.\n10\t- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.AgentTask`, it composes the\n11\t  prompt via :func:`~darkfactory.templates.compose_prompt`, picks the\n12\t  model (explicit override > capability mapping > sonnet fallback),\n13\t  invokes Claude Code via :func:`~darkfactory.invoke.invoke_claude`,\n14\t  and stores the output on the context.\n15\t- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.ShellTask`, it runs the\n16\t  formatted command and handles the configured ``on_failure`` policy.\n17\t\n18\tThe runner does **not** know how to create branches, manage\n19\tworktrees, or open PRs — those are built-in tasks. Its only job is\n20\tthe dispatch loop and the retry-on-failure bookkeeping.\n21\t\n22\tRetry semantics: when a ShellTask fails with\n23\t``on_failure=\"retry_agent\"``, the runner looks backward in the task\n24\tlist for the most recent AgentTask, re-invokes it with the failed\n25\toutput bound to ``{{CHECK_OUTPUT}}``, and re-runs the failed shell\n26\ttask once. If it still fails, the runner gives up and marks the\n27\tPRD blocked (via a separate ``set_status`` built-in call).\n28\t\n29\tDry-run mode: when ``ctx.dry_run=True``, every built-in and shell\n30\ttask logs what it would do without executing. Agent tasks return a\n31\tsynthetic success result via :func:`~darkfactory.invoke.invoke_claude`'s\n32\t``dry_run=True`` path. This is what ``prd plan`` uses.\n33\t\"\"\"\n34\t\n35\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n36\t\n37\timport logging\n38\timport subprocess\n39\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\n40\tfrom pathlib import Path\n41\tfrom typing import TYPE_CHECKING\n42\t\n43\tfrom .builtins import BUILTINS\n44\tfrom .invoke import InvokeResult, capability_to_model, invoke_claude\n45\tfrom .templates import compose_prompt\n46\tfrom .workflow import (\n47\t    AgentTask,\n48\t    BuiltIn,\n49\t    ExecutionContext,\n50\t    ShellTask,\n51\t    Task,\n52\t    Workflow,\n53\t)\n54\t\n55\tif TYPE_CHECKING:\n56\t    from .prd import PRD\n57\t    from .style import Styler\n58\t\n59\t\n60\tlogger = logging.getLogger(\"darkfactory.runner\")\n61\t\n62\t\n63\t@dataclass\n64\tclass TaskStep:\n65\t    \"\"\"A single executed task step and its outcome.\n66\t\n67\t    Used by :class:`RunResult` to record what actually happened during\n68\t    a workflow run, for both success reporting and debugging failures.\n69\t    \"\"\"\n70\t\n71\t    name: str\n72\t    kind: str  # \"builtin\" | \"agent\" | \"shell\"\n73\t    success: bool\n74\t    detail: str = \"\"\n75\t\n76\t\n77\t@dataclass\n78\tclass RunResult:\n79\t    \"\"\"Structured outcome of a workflow run.\n80\t\n81\t    The runner populates this as it walks the task list. On success,\n82\t    ``success=True`` and ``pr_url`` is set (assuming the workflow\n83\t    includes a ``create_pr`` built-in). On failure, ``success=False``\n84\t    and ``failure_reason`` describes what went wrong; ``steps`` is\n85\t    still populated with every step that completed before the failure.\n86\t    \"\"\"\n87\t\n88\t    success: bool\n89\t    pr_url: str | None = None\n90\t    steps: list[TaskStep] = field(default_factory=list)\n91\t    failure_reason: str | None = None\n92\t\n93\t\n94\tdef _compute_branch_name(prd: \"PRD\") -> str:\n95\t    \"\"\"Derive the branch name a workflow should use for this PRD.\n96\t\n97\t    Matches the convention in ``ensure_worktree``:\n98\t    ``prd/<id>-<slug>``. Surfaced as a helper so callers can compute\n99\t    it before creating the ExecutionContext.\n100\t    \"\"\""}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"52744e12-d8b3-437c-a43e-6547c29dff12","uuid":"5e1b81ce-7d44-4846-b2b1-74ba7f752f9f","timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:16:23.021Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-224.3-summarize-agent-run/src/darkfactory/runner.py","content":"\"\"\"Workflow execution engine — walks a workflow's tasks against a context.\n\nThe runner is the glue between every other module in the harness:\n\n- It holds an :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.ExecutionContext` and\n  threads it through the task list.\n- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.BuiltIn`, it looks up the\n  named function in :data:`~darkfactory.builtins.BUILTINS` and calls\n  it with the context + formatted kwargs.\n- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.AgentTask`, it composes the\n  prompt via :func:`~darkfactory.templates.compose_prompt`, picks the\n  model (explicit override > capability mapping > sonnet fallback),\n  invokes Claude Code via :func:`~darkfactory.invoke.invoke_claude`,\n  and stores the output on the context.\n- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.ShellTask`, it runs the\n  formatted command and handles the configured ``on_failure`` policy.\n\nThe runner does **not** know how to create branches, manage\nworktrees, or open PRs — those are built-in tasks. Its only job is\nthe dispatch loop and the retry-on-failure bookkeeping.\n\nRetry semantics: when a ShellTask fails with\n``on_failure=\"retry_agent\"``, the runner looks backward in the task\nlist for the most recent AgentTask, re-invokes it with the failed\noutput bound to ``{{CHECK_OUTPUT}}``, and re-runs the failed shell\ntask once. If it still fails, the runner gives up and marks the\nPRD blocked (via a separate ``set_status`` built-in call).\n\nDry-run mode: when ``ctx.dry_run=True``, every built-in and shell\ntask logs what it would do without executing. Agent tasks return a\nsynthetic success result via :func:`~darkfactory.invoke.invoke_claude`'s\n``dry_run=True`` path. This is what ``prd plan`` uses.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nimport subprocess\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import TYPE_CHECKING\n\nfrom .builtins import BUILTINS\nfrom .invoke import InvokeResult, capability_to_model, invoke_claude\nfrom .templates import compose_prompt\nfrom .workflow import (\n    AgentTask,\n    BuiltIn,\n    ExecutionContext,\n    ShellTask,\n    Task,\n    Workflow,\n)\n\nif TYPE_CHECKING:\n    from .prd import PRD\n    from .style import Styler\n\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(\"darkfactory.runner\")\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass TaskStep:\n    \"\"\"A single executed task step and its outcome.\n\n    Used by :class:`RunResult` to record what actually happened during\n    a workflow run, for both success reporting and debugging failures.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    name: str\n    kind: str  # \"builtin\" | \"agent\" | \"shell\"\n    success: bool\n    detail: str = \"\"\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass RunResult:\n    \"\"\"Structured outcome of a workflow run.\n\n    The runner populates this as it walks the task list. On success,\n    ``success=True`` and ``pr_url`` is set (assuming the workflow\n    includes a ``create_pr`` built-in). On failure, ``success=False``\n    and ``failure_reason`` describes what went wrong; ``steps`` is\n    still populated with every step that completed before the failure.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    success: bool\n    pr_url: str | None = None\n    steps: list[TaskStep] = field(default_factory=list)\n    failure_reason: str | None = None\n\n\ndef _compute_branch_name(prd: \"PRD\") -> str:\n    \"\"\"Derive the branch name a workflow should use for this PRD.\n\n    Matches the convention in ``ensure_worktree``:\n    ``prd/<id>-<slug>``. Surfaced as a helper so callers can compute\n    it before creating the ExecutionContext.\n    \"\"\"","numLines":100,"startLine":1,"totalLines":463}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VH4tgy52SgfkZxkox4Zs7W","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LbWgyrxSg89GfAaq8wrW3v","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-224.3-summarize-agent-run/src/darkfactory/runner.py","offset":100,"limit":200},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1307,"cache_read_input_tokens":43411,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1307},"output_tokens":69,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"52744e12-d8b3-437c-a43e-6547c29dff12","uuid":"69446e10-5543-43fe-b60d-4e2f423111ef"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LbWgyrxSg89GfAaq8wrW3v","type":"tool_result","content":"100\t    \"\"\"\n101\t    return f\"prd/{prd.id}-{prd.slug}\"\n102\t\n103\t\n104\tdef _pick_model(task: AgentTask, prd: \"PRD\", override: str | None = None) -> str:\n105\t    \"\"\"Resolve the model to use for an AgentTask invocation.\n106\t\n107\t    Priority: CLI override > task.model > capability-derived > sonnet.\n108\t    \"\"\"\n109\t    if override:\n110\t        return override\n111\t    if task.model:\n112\t        return task.model\n113\t    if task.model_from_capability:\n114\t        return capability_to_model(prd.capability)\n115\t    return \"sonnet\"\n116\t\n117\t\n118\tdef run_workflow(\n119\t    prd: \"PRD\",\n120\t    workflow: Workflow,\n121\t    repo_root: Path,\n122\t    base_ref: str,\n123\t    *,\n124\t    dry_run: bool = True,\n125\t    model_override: str | None = None,\n126\t    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n127\t) -> RunResult:\n128\t    \"\"\"Execute a workflow against a single PRD and return the result.\n129\t\n130\t    Builds an :class:`ExecutionContext` and dispatches each task in\n131\t    ``workflow.tasks`` in order. Tasks mutate the context as they run\n132\t    (set worktree path, store agent output, capture PR URL). On any\n133\t    uncaught exception, returns a failure result with the partial\n134\t    ``steps`` list so the caller can see what completed.\n135\t\n136\t    ``dry_run=True`` (default) makes every task log instead of\n137\t    executing — safe to call on arbitrary PRDs.\n138\t    \"\"\"\n139\t    branch_name = _compute_branch_name(prd)\n140\t    ctx = ExecutionContext(\n141\t        prd=prd,\n142\t        repo_root=repo_root,\n143\t        workflow=workflow,\n144\t        base_ref=base_ref,\n145\t        branch_name=branch_name,\n146\t        cwd=repo_root,\n147\t        dry_run=dry_run,\n148\t        logger=logger,\n149\t    )\n150\t\n151\t    result = RunResult(success=True)\n152\t    # Track the last AgentTask so a later ShellTask with\n153\t    # on_failure=retry_agent can re-invoke it.\n154\t    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None = None\n155\t    last_agent_result: InvokeResult | None = None\n156\t\n157\t    try:\n158\t        for task in workflow.tasks:\n159\t            try:\n160\t                step = _dispatch(\n161\t                    task,\n162\t                    ctx,\n163\t                    model_override,\n164\t                    last_agent_task,\n165\t                    last_agent_result,\n166\t                    styler=styler,\n167\t                )\n168\t                result.steps.append(step)\n169\t\n170\t                if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n171\t                    last_agent_task = task\n172\t                    # We can't easily reach the InvokeResult from _dispatch without\n173\t                    # restructuring, so we re-record it here via a side channel:\n174\t                    # _dispatch stores the agent result on the context.\n175\t                    last_agent_result = getattr(ctx, \"_last_agent_result\", None)\n176\t\n177\t                if not step.success:\n178\t                    result.success = False\n179\t                    result.failure_reason = step.detail or f\"task {step.name!r} failed\"\n180\t                    break\n181\t            except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001 — we want to log any failure\n182\t                result.success = False\n183\t                result.failure_reason = f\"task {_task_name(task)!r} raised: {exc}\"\n184\t                result.steps.append(\n185\t                    TaskStep(\n186\t                        name=_task_name(task),\n187\t                        kind=_task_kind(task),\n188\t                        success=False,\n189\t                        detail=str(exc),\n190\t                    )\n191\t                )\n192\t                break\n193\t    finally:\n194\t        _release_worktree_lock(ctx)\n195\t\n196\t    result.pr_url = ctx.pr_url\n197\t    return result\n198\t\n199\t\n200\tdef _release_worktree_lock(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None:\n201\t    \"\"\"Release the advisory lock acquired by ensure_worktree, if any.\n202\t\n203\t    Safe to call multiple times and on contexts that never acquired a\n204\t    lock (e.g. dry-run paths).\n205\t    \"\"\"\n206\t    lock = ctx._worktree_lock\n207\t    if lock is None:\n208\t        return\n209\t    try:\n210\t        lock.release()\n211\t    except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n212\t        ctx.logger.warning(\"failed to release worktree lock: %s\", exc)\n213\t    finally:\n214\t        ctx._worktree_lock = None\n215\t\n216\t\n217\tdef _task_name(task: Task) -> str:\n218\t    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n219\t        return task.name\n220\t    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n221\t        return task.name\n222\t    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n223\t        return task.name\n224\t    return type(task).__name__\n225\t\n226\t\n227\tdef _task_kind(task: Task) -> str:\n228\t    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n229\t        return \"builtin\"\n230\t    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n231\t        return \"agent\"\n232\t    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n233\t        return \"shell\"\n234\t    return \"unknown\"\n235\t\n236\t\n237\tdef _dispatch(\n238\t    task: Task,\n239\t    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n240\t    model_override: str | None,\n241\t    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None,\n242\t    last_agent_result: InvokeResult | None,\n243\t    *,\n244\t    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n245\t) -> TaskStep:\n246\t    \"\"\"Dispatch a single task by type and return a TaskStep describing the outcome.\"\"\"\n247\t    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n248\t        return _run_builtin(task, ctx)\n249\t    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n250\t        return _run_agent(task, ctx, model_override, styler=styler)\n251\t    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n252\t        return _run_shell(task, ctx, last_agent_task, model_override, styler=styler)\n253\t    raise TypeError(f\"unknown task type: {type(task).__name__}\")\n254\t\n255\t\n256\tdef _run_builtin(task: BuiltIn, ctx: ExecutionContext) -> TaskStep:\n257\t    \"\"\"Look up the built-in by name and call it with formatted kwargs.\"\"\"\n258\t    if task.name not in BUILTINS:\n259\t        return TaskStep(\n260\t            name=task.name,\n261\t            kind=\"builtin\",\n262\t            success=False,\n263\t            detail=f\"no builtin registered for {task.name!r}\",\n264\t        )\n265\t\n266\t    func = BUILTINS[task.name]\n267\t\n268\t    # Format any string kwargs against the context (e.g. commit messages\n269\t    # like \"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\").\n270\t    formatted_kwargs: dict[str, object] = {}\n271\t    for key, value in task.kwargs.items():\n272\t        if isinstance(value, str):\n273\t            formatted_kwargs[key] = ctx.format_string(value)\n274\t        else:\n275\t            formatted_kwargs[key] = value\n276\t\n277\t    func(ctx, **formatted_kwargs)\n278\t    return TaskStep(name=task.name, kind=\"builtin\", success=True)\n279\t\n280\t\n281\tdef _run_agent(\n282\t    task: AgentTask,\n283\t    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n284\t    model_override: str | None,\n285\t    *,\n286\t    extras: dict[str, object] | None = None,\n287\t    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n288\t) -> TaskStep:\n289\t    \"\"\"Compose prompts, invoke Claude Code, and record the result on context.\"\"\"\n290\t    prompt = compose_prompt(ctx.workflow, task.prompts, ctx, extras=extras)\n291\t    model = _pick_model(task, ctx.prd, override=model_override)\n292\t\n293\t    result = invoke_claude(\n294\t        prompt=prompt,\n295\t        tools=task.tools,\n296\t        model=model,\n297\t        cwd=ctx.cwd,\n298\t        sentinel_success=task.sentinel_success,\n299\t        sentinel_failure=task.sentinel_failure,"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"52744e12-d8b3-437c-a43e-6547c29dff12","uuid":"fb990f24-f0fc-4190-a003-09d980320f16","timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:16:25.247Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-224.3-summarize-agent-run/src/darkfactory/runner.py","content":"    \"\"\"\n    return f\"prd/{prd.id}-{prd.slug}\"\n\n\ndef _pick_model(task: AgentTask, prd: \"PRD\", override: str | None = None) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Resolve the model to use for an AgentTask invocation.\n\n    Priority: CLI override > task.model > capability-derived > sonnet.\n    \"\"\"\n    if override:\n        return override\n    if task.model:\n        return task.model\n    if task.model_from_capability:\n        return capability_to_model(prd.capability)\n    return \"sonnet\"\n\n\ndef run_workflow(\n    prd: \"PRD\",\n    workflow: Workflow,\n    repo_root: Path,\n    base_ref: str,\n    *,\n    dry_run: bool = True,\n    model_override: str | None = None,\n    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n) -> RunResult:\n    \"\"\"Execute a workflow against a single PRD and return the result.\n\n    Builds an :class:`ExecutionContext` and dispatches each task in\n    ``workflow.tasks`` in order. Tasks mutate the context as they run\n    (set worktree path, store agent output, capture PR URL). On any\n    uncaught exception, returns a failure result with the partial\n    ``steps`` list so the caller can see what completed.\n\n    ``dry_run=True`` (default) makes every task log instead of\n    executing — safe to call on arbitrary PRDs.\n    \"\"\"\n    branch_name = _compute_branch_name(prd)\n    ctx = ExecutionContext(\n        prd=prd,\n        repo_root=repo_root,\n        workflow=workflow,\n        base_ref=base_ref,\n        branch_name=branch_name,\n        cwd=repo_root,\n        dry_run=dry_run,\n        logger=logger,\n    )\n\n    result = RunResult(success=True)\n    # Track the last AgentTask so a later ShellTask with\n    # on_failure=retry_agent can re-invoke it.\n    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None = None\n    last_agent_result: InvokeResult | None = None\n\n    try:\n        for task in workflow.tasks:\n            try:\n                step = _dispatch(\n                    task,\n                    ctx,\n                    model_override,\n                    last_agent_task,\n                    last_agent_result,\n                    styler=styler,\n                )\n                result.steps.append(step)\n\n                if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n                    last_agent_task = task\n                    # We can't easily reach the InvokeResult from _dispatch without\n                    # restructuring, so we re-record it here via a side channel:\n                    # _dispatch stores the agent result on the context.\n                    last_agent_result = getattr(ctx, \"_last_agent_result\", None)\n\n                if not step.success:\n                    result.success = False\n                    result.failure_reason = step.detail or f\"task {step.name!r} failed\"\n                    break\n            except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001 — we want to log any failure\n                result.success = False\n                result.failure_reason = f\"task {_task_name(task)!r} raised: {exc}\"\n                result.steps.append(\n                    TaskStep(\n                        name=_task_name(task),\n                        kind=_task_kind(task),\n                        success=False,\n                        detail=str(exc),\n                    )\n                )\n                break\n    finally:\n        _release_worktree_lock(ctx)\n\n    result.pr_url = ctx.pr_url\n    return result\n\n\ndef _release_worktree_lock(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Release the advisory lock acquired by ensure_worktree, if any.\n\n    Safe to call multiple times and on contexts that never acquired a\n    lock (e.g. dry-run paths).\n    \"\"\"\n    lock = ctx._worktree_lock\n    if lock is None:\n        return\n    try:\n        lock.release()\n    except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n        ctx.logger.warning(\"failed to release worktree lock: %s\", exc)\n    finally:\n        ctx._worktree_lock = None\n\n\ndef _task_name(task: Task) -> str:\n    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n        return task.name\n    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n        return task.name\n    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n        return task.name\n    return type(task).__name__\n\n\ndef _task_kind(task: Task) -> str:\n    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n        return \"builtin\"\n    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n        return \"agent\"\n    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n        return \"shell\"\n    return \"unknown\"\n\n\ndef _dispatch(\n    task: Task,\n    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n    model_override: str | None,\n    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None,\n    last_agent_result: InvokeResult | None,\n    *,\n    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n) -> TaskStep:\n    \"\"\"Dispatch a single task by type and return a TaskStep describing the outcome.\"\"\"\n    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n        return _run_builtin(task, ctx)\n    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n        return _run_agent(task, ctx, model_override, styler=styler)\n    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n        return _run_shell(task, ctx, last_agent_task, model_override, styler=styler)\n    raise TypeError(f\"unknown task type: {type(task).__name__}\")\n\n\ndef _run_builtin(task: BuiltIn, ctx: ExecutionContext) -> TaskStep:\n    \"\"\"Look up the built-in by name and call it with formatted kwargs.\"\"\"\n    if task.name not in BUILTINS:\n        return TaskStep(\n            name=task.name,\n            kind=\"builtin\",\n            success=False,\n            detail=f\"no builtin registered for {task.name!r}\",\n        )\n\n    func = BUILTINS[task.name]\n\n    # Format any string kwargs against the context (e.g. commit messages\n    # like \"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\").\n    formatted_kwargs: dict[str, object] = {}\n    for key, value in task.kwargs.items():\n        if isinstance(value, str):\n            formatted_kwargs[key] = ctx.format_string(value)\n        else:\n            formatted_kwargs[key] = value\n\n    func(ctx, **formatted_kwargs)\n    return TaskStep(name=task.name, kind=\"builtin\", success=True)\n\n\ndef _run_agent(\n    task: AgentTask,\n    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n    model_override: str | None,\n    *,\n    extras: dict[str, object] | None = None,\n    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n) -> TaskStep:\n    \"\"\"Compose prompts, invoke Claude Code, and record the result on context.\"\"\"\n    prompt = compose_prompt(ctx.workflow, task.prompts, ctx, extras=extras)\n    model = _pick_model(task, ctx.prd, override=model_override)\n\n    result = invoke_claude(\n        prompt=prompt,\n        tools=task.tools,\n        model=model,\n        cwd=ctx.cwd,\n        sentinel_success=task.sentinel_success,\n        sentinel_failure=task.sentinel_failure,","numLines":200,"startLine":100,"totalLines":463}}}
